{"title": "Paul and Virginia", "description": "Paul and Virginia was first published in 1787. The novel's title characters are very good friends since birth who fall in love, but sadly die when the ship Le Saint-Geran is wrecked. The story is set in the island of Mauritius under French rule, then named \u00cele de France, which the author had visited. Written on the eve of the French Revolution, the novel is hailed as Bernardin's finest work. It records the fate of a child of nature corrupted by the false, artificial sentimentality that prevailed at the time among the upper classes of France.(Summary by Wikipedia)", "duration": 18716, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "5318", "name": " Jacques-Henri Bernardin de Saint-Pierre"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt5/Paul_and_Virginia_1007.jpg", "copyright_year": "1787", "genres": ["General Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Ellis Christoff"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Ellis Christoff"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Bart de Leeuw"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Jeanie"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface", "readers": [2288], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/paul_and_virginia_1007_librivox/paulandvirginia_00_bernardindestpierre_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2408}, {"section": 1, "title": "Part 01", "readers": [2288], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/paul_and_virginia_1007_librivox/paulandvirginia_01_bernardindestpierre_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1738}, {"section": 2, "title": "Part 02", "readers": [2288], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/paul_and_virginia_1007_librivox/paulandvirginia_02_bernardindestpierre_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1538}, {"section": 3, "title": "Part 03", "readers": [2288], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/paul_and_virginia_1007_librivox/paulandvirginia_03_bernardindestpierre_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2070}, {"section": 4, "title": "Part 04", "readers": [2288], "path": "https://www.arc